coming up.

37:56.408 --> 37:58.281
- I need new material.
- I know.

37:58.283 --> 38:00.114
I know. I'm just saying
he's sensitive.

38:00.116 --> 38:02.573
- That's all.
- You and me go back a long way.

38:02.575 --> 38:04.448
- I painted you once, remember?
- I remember.

38:04.450 --> 38:07.156
I'm hanging
in a gallery somewhere. It's...

38:07.158 --> 38:08.073
I've been stale for years

38:08.075 --> 38:10.656
and you were too polite
to tell me the truth.

38:10.658 --> 38:12.073
It's been hard. I get it.

38:12.075 --> 38:14.489
And muses are thin
on the ground these days.

38:14.491 --> 38:18.906
Just... break him in gently.
Please.

38:18.908 --> 38:20.114
If he wants to be a muse

38:20.116 --> 38:23.323
he'll have to put the work in,
simple as that.

38:23.325 --> 38:25.823
Because when it comes
to the male form,

38:25.825 --> 38:28.783
I am an incurable romantic.

38:29.741 --> 38:31.739
If being a muse was easy,
every Tom...

38:31.741 --> 38:35.281
- Tom, Dick and Harry, yes.
- Don't take the piss.

38:35.283 --> 38:36.489
Just give me six months
with him.

38:36.491 --> 38:39.156
Six months?
How much are you paying him?

38:39.158 --> 38:42.239
How much does he get
for the other stuff?

38:43.158 --> 38:46.406
How much? Jesus Christ,
I'm in the wrong game.

38:46.408 --> 38:49.448
I used to be quite a looker
in my time, you know.

38:49.450 --> 38:52.033
Well, everyone said it.

38:54.616 --> 38:56.614
Do you believe in fate, Jim?

38:56.616 --> 38:57.531
I do, actually, yeah.

38:57.533 --> 39:00.406
Then it's fate
that has brought us together.

39:00.408 --> 39:05.448
I'll expect you every day
at 8pm sharp, except Sunday.

39:05.450 --> 39:06.948
We'll work through the night.

39:06.950 --> 39:09.114
I won't tolerate
any bad timekeeping.

39:09.116 --> 39:10.281
Yes, sir.

39:10.283 --> 39:12.698
Beauty will only get you so far
in this business.

39:12.700 --> 39:16.406
You have to dedicate yourself.
You have to concentrate.

39:16.408 --> 39:17.864
I wanna do this, Max,
I really do.

39:17.866 --> 39:21.448
I'm going to request
that you do not move,

39:21.450 --> 39:22.531
that you do not speak.

39:22.533 --> 39:25.614
After we finish
you can talk all you like.

39:25.616 --> 39:27.864
I'm tired of talking,
to tell you the truth.

39:27.866 --> 39:30.281
Talking just gets me
into trouble.

39:30.283 --> 39:30.948
Good.

39:30.950 --> 39:33.575
Let's get down to work, then.

40:16.991 --> 40:18.781
I particularly like
the tension

40:18.783 --> 40:25.073
between the beauty of the image
and the violence of the pose.

40:25.075 --> 40:28.156
The taut muscles,
the clenched fists.

40:28.158 --> 40:31.531
The thickness of the paint,
the bold strokes.

40:31.533 --> 40:35.281
I can't believe I've finally
made it onto a canvas.

40:35.283 --> 40:37.114
And this is just the beginning.

40:37.116 --> 40:39.864
I imagine a whole series
of paintings,

40:39.866 --> 40:41.281
exploring every facet of...

40:41.283 --> 40:43.950
All you all right?

40:44.450 --> 40:44.948
Yeah.

40:44.950 --> 40:47.781
Yeah, no, I just... I've been
sat in here for months.

40:47.783 --> 40:49.864
I need to get some fresh air,
that's all.

40:49.866 --> 40:53.991
I wish
I had your problems.

41:27.950 --> 41:30.156
What happened to you?
You look like shit, mate.

41:30.158 --> 41:34.364
It's nice to see you, too. I've
been working a lot, that's all.

41:34.366 --> 41:35.573
What, you call that work?

41:35.575 --> 41:38.948
Sitting on your arse all day
and getting paid for it?

41:38.950 --> 41:40.906
You did all right for yourself
in the end.

41:40.908 --> 41:43.614
And you can say it was me
who discovered you.

41:43.616 --> 41:44.989
What are you talking about?

41:44.991 --> 41:48.448
I was the one who brought you to
that bar that night, remember?

41:48.450 --> 41:51.948
It was me who took you
under my wing, so to speak,

41:51.950 --> 41:54.323
on the path to fame and fortune.

41:54.325 --> 41:54.864
Hang on a minute.

41:54.866 --> 41:57.739
Weren't you the one who tried
to charge me ten quid a night

41:57.741 --> 41:59.906
- to sleep in a cardboard box?
- Listen.

41:59.908 --> 42:02.948
Why are all rent boys
so cynical these days?

42:02.950 --> 42:05.239
I'm not a rent boy, I'm a muse.

42:05.241 --> 42:05.698
Exactly!

42:05.700 --> 42:06.656
And muse ain't the type of job

42:06.658 --> 42:08.906
you see advertised
in the job centre, is it?

42:08.908 --> 42:12.741
Being in the right place
at the right time.

42:13.616 --> 42:14.114
You know what?

42:14.116 --> 42:17.073
I think I'm beginning to see
what all the fuss is about.

42:17.075 --> 42:19.239
Stop touching my face.

42:19.241 --> 42:20.364
Oh, you reckon cos I'm homeless,

42:20.366 --> 42:24.616
I can't appreciate
good bone structure?

42:25.866 --> 42:31.698
Listen, mate, are you all right?
You're acting well weird.

42:38.075 --> 42:39.073
Fuck me.

42:39.075 --> 42:41.700
Youaretired.

43:39.658 --> 43:40.531
What's going on?

43:40.533 --> 43:43.114
I was about to ask you
the same question.

43:43.116 --> 43:43.781
We're worried about you.

43:43.783 --> 43:46.031
I'm worried too. I don't know
what's wrong with me.

43:46.033 --> 43:47.448
Being sensitive
is all well and good,

43:47.450 --> 43:49.364
but you can't be fainting
every five minutes.

43:49.366 --> 43:51.906
- It makes people nervous.
- The sex I can deal with.

43:51.908 --> 43:55.114
- It's the art that fucks me up.
- Tell us what's been happening.

43:55.116 --> 43:58.614
Go from the beginning,
before you met us, I mean.

44:00.283 --> 44:01.656
OK.

44:01.658 --> 44:03.864
Er...

44:03.866 --> 44:04.823
It was my last year at school

44:04.825 --> 44:07.114
and all I could think about
was moving to London.

44:07.116 --> 44:09.948
But I had a thing for my
art teacher. And I'd do anything

44:09.950 --> 44:11.864
- to catch a glimpse of him.
- You had it bad.

44:11.866 --> 44:14.281
Really bad. I've got a thing
for educated people

44:14.283 --> 44:18.364
and this bloke had practically
swallowed a dictionary.

44:18.366 --> 44:21.948
Late one night, he lured me into
the corner of the library,

44:21.950 --> 44:24.614
and showed me
some disturbing images.

44:24.616 --> 44:26.031
- What? Porn?
- No.

44:26.033 --> 44:29.448
It was art, but like nothing
I'd ever seen before.

44:29.450 --> 44:30.198
Now I know it was Baroque,

44:30.200 --> 44:33.364
but back then, I didn't know
what the fuck was going on.

44:33.366 --> 44:34.031
Don't get me wrong,

44:34.033 --> 44:36.406
the naked bodies were a turn-on,
it's just...

44:36.408 --> 44:37.406
Did he ever touch you?

44:37.408 --> 44:40.781
No. He just stared at me
for hours.

44:40.783 --> 44:42.239
He objectified you.

44:42.241 --> 44:44.531
I was proper objectified, yeah.

44:44.533 --> 44:46.406
But that was when
it got more serious

44:46.408 --> 44:47.948
and we started going
to galleries,

44:47.950 --> 44:50.281
and whilst I stared
at the paintings,

44:50.283 --> 44:50.948
he'd be staring at me.

44:50.950 --> 44:54.364
Did you tell the police?
Social services?

44:54.366 --> 44:57.948
No, I secretly enjoyed
the attention.

44:57.950 --> 45:00.239
But that's when
I started to get sick.

45:00.241 --> 45:01.656
I saw myself in the paintings.

45:01.658 --> 45:04.114
So, let me get this straight.

45:04.116 --> 45:05.489
We have a sensitive teenage boy

45:05.491 --> 45:07.739
coming to terms
with his sexuality

45:07.741 --> 45:09.698
and a highly intelligent
older male

45:09.700 --> 45:12.364
who uses art
as a means of seduction.

45:12.366 --> 45:13.948
Correct.

45:13.950 --> 45:15.073
To complicate matters further,

45:15.075 --> 45:18.156
and for reasons we don't
yet understand, said teenage boy

45:18.158 --> 45:20.573
can't look
at a beautiful painting

45:20.575 --> 45:22.614
without feeling
emotionally overwhelmed,

45:22.616 --> 45:24.739
without imagining himself in it.

45:24.741 --> 45:26.364
Also correct.

45:26.366 --> 45:28.031
We need to get you to a doctor.

45:28.033 --> 45:30.489
Maybe I should just
avoid art galleries.

45:30.491 --> 45:33.323
That's impossible in
our line of work, you know that.

45:33.325 --> 45:35.656
I'm thinking
of changing my career.

45:35.658 --> 45:37.281
Don't be too hasty.

45:37.283 --> 45:39.698
I know the person
you should see.

45:39.700 --> 45:41.531
- You do?
- I do.

45:41.533 --> 45:45.406
She's not cheap
but she's good at what she does.

45:45.408 --> 45:46.531
What does she do?

45:46.533 --> 45:50.866
She specialises in illnesses
no one's ever heard of.

45:53.241 --> 45:55.573
Give her a call.

45:55.575 --> 45:58.573
Come on, handsome. Don't be shy.

46:00.450 --> 46:06.781
Jim, why do you think Caravaggio
has been such a problem for you?

46:06.783 --> 46:08.614
Oh, don't get me wrong,
I'm a big fan.

46:08.616 --> 46:10.448
For me,
it's where modern art started.

46:10.450 --> 46:13.489
And you feel a compulsion
to return to him,

46:13.491 --> 46:15.573
to study his work again
and again?

46:15.575 --> 46:17.198
Look, Caravaggio probably wasn't

46:17.200 --> 46:18.698
the greatest artist
who ever lived.

46:18.700 --> 46:22.864
Technically, I mean, but the way
he painted darkness and light,

46:22.866 --> 46:25.156
he was brilliant,
no one could touch him.

46:25.158 --> 46:26.906
And what about
the people he painted?

46:26.908 --> 46:30.114
The tricksters, the whores,
the undesirables?

46:30.116 --> 46:33.323
I love the fact he took
ordinary people from the street

46:33.325 --> 46:36.864
and made 'em look like saints.
He was the first one to do that.

46:36.866 --> 46:39.864
Do you identify with the people
in his paintings?

46:39.866 --> 46:42.781
I do, yeah.
I feel like I know them.

46:42.783 --> 46:45.741
They could be me or my mates.

46:45.991 --> 46:48.656
Would you consider yourself
a religious person?

46:48.658 --> 46:52.823
Not really.
I just imagine the worst.

46:52.825 --> 46:56.656
When I see Baby Jesus, I just
think about the crucifixion.

46:56.658 --> 46:59.614
All that pain and suffering
really gets to me.

46:59.616 --> 47:05.783
And the beauty of it just
draws me in and... won't let go.

47:05.991 --> 47:08.906
Jim, there are a number
of syndromes

47:08.908 --> 47:12.864
associated with these kinds
of reactions to art,

47:12.866 --> 47:15.614
from mild anxiety
to severe delusional states.

47:15.616 --> 47:19.364
Do you think I'm on
the high end of the spectrum?

47:19.366 --> 47:22.950
Well, that's what
we're about to discover.

47:23.866 --> 47:26.906
Try and stay calm.

47:26.908 --> 47:29.489
I'm going to remove
your blindfold.

47:29.491 --> 47:33.698
And when I do, we'll approach
the painting together.

47:33.700 --> 47:36.906
And I want you
to describe what you see.

47:36.908 --> 47:39.033
OK?

47:56.533 --> 47:59.075
The Musicians.

48:00.908 --> 48:02.698
It's beautiful, isn't it?

48:02.700 --> 48:06.948
Hmm. It's a beautiful painting,
yes, but what else?

48:06.950 --> 48:09.741
What else do you see?

48:10.908 --> 48:13.031
I see myself.

48:13.033 --> 48:15.575
There, look.

48:18.325 --> 48:21.116
Music. I can hear music.

48:21.575 --> 48:24.616
Like tuning of instruments.

48:38.783 --> 48:40.073
What are you lot doing here?

48:40.075 --> 48:44.531
Italian bloke. The one
with the mad glint in his eye.

48:44.533 --> 48:45.406
Caravaggio.

48:45.408 --> 48:46.698
Yeah, whatever his name is.

48:46.700 --> 48:49.948
He was wandering round Soho
looking confused.

48:49.950 --> 48:51.656
At first I thought
he was homeless,

48:51.658 --> 48:53.114
but it turns out
he's proper famous.

48:53.116 --> 48:56.156
He's famous, all right,
but he can be very tricky.

48:56.158 --> 48:58.781
Yeah. He definitely had
a few too many.

48:58.783 --> 49:00.948
You could smell it
on his breath.

49:00.950 --> 49:04.781
Anyway, he offered me a few gold
coins and a warm bed at night,

49:04.783 --> 49:08.198
if I... dressed up as Cupid.

49:08.200 --> 49:08.823
What's up with you?

49:08.825 --> 49:11.948
I'm having a check-up on the
state of my mental well-being

49:11.950 --> 49:14.364
from a doctor
who was once a prostitute.

49:14.366 --> 49:17.448
Fair enough.
Is she fit?

49:17.450 --> 49:21.783
You need to be quiet.
He looks pissed off.

49:22.950 --> 49:25.491
Oh, fuck, here he comes.

49:34.033 --> 49:34.698
Call me old-fashioned,

49:34.700 --> 49:36.739
but pretty boys are supposed
to pose for the artist

49:36.741 --> 49:39.073
- and keep their mouths shut.
- We were just saying...

49:39.075 --> 49:41.781
Have you ever tried working
with this much noise going on?

49:41.783 --> 49:45.614
- You should try it some time.
- You need to take a chill pill.

49:45.616 --> 49:47.364
It's just a bit of banter.

49:47.366 --> 49:50.989
Remember, this is one
of your lightest pieces.

49:50.991 --> 49:53.448
You boys make me want to puke.

49:53.450 --> 49:54.906
Thinking you're better
than anyone else

49:54.908 --> 49:58.114
just cos you're hanging
in a gallery somewhere.

49:58.116 --> 49:59.406
Who gives a shit?

49:59.408 --> 50:01.739
You were the one who chose us,
remember?

50:01.741 --> 50:03.864
You plucked us from obscurity.

50:03.866 --> 50:06.281
It's tough working in this town,
you know.

50:06.283 --> 50:08.156
Roman cardinals
can be very picky.

50:08.158 --> 50:11.616
And don't even get me started
on the Pope.

50:12.908 --> 50:17.864
No one ever asks Caravaggio
if he's having a nice day.

50:17.866 --> 50:18.781
What's this guy's problem?

50:18.783 --> 50:21.781
I think the problem
is he's a tortured genius.

50:21.783 --> 50:24.156
I'll tell you
what the problem is.

50:24.158 --> 50:28.656
I have boys queueing round the
block to sit where you are now.

50:28.658 --> 50:31.489
So, any more bullshit
from you...

50:31.491 --> 50:34.323
and I'll throw you back to the
gutter where you belong.

50:34.325 --> 50:36.823
- Understood?
- Understood.

50:36.825 --> 50:39.989
I make you and your boyfriends
pretty in my paintings,

50:39.991 --> 50:43.200
so don't fuck with me!

50:44.241 --> 50:46.408
OK?

50:53.158 --> 50:55.739
Caravaggio,
temperamental genius.

50:55.741 --> 50:56.739
Fugitive from the law.

50:56.741 --> 51:01.325
- Apparently a homo.
- Definitely a nutter.

51:05.200 --> 51:10.408
Jim, where did you think
you were?

51:12.200 --> 51:13.989
I imagined I was in Rome

51:13.991 --> 51:16.364
in the summer of 1595.

51:16.366 --> 51:19.323
In the home
of Cardinal del Monte,

51:19.325 --> 51:21.281
being painted by Caravaggio.

51:21.283 --> 51:22.656
I was one of the musicians.

51:22.658 --> 51:24.239
We were just tuning
our instruments,

51:24.241 --> 51:26.781
minding our own business
when it all kicked off.

51:26.783 --> 51:30.073
In what sense did it...
kick off?

51:30.075 --> 51:34.198
Look, I know Caravaggio's
got a lot on his plate:

51:34.200 --> 51:37.573
murder, illness,
exiled to Sicily.

51:37.575 --> 51:39.739
It's just...
He needs to chill out a bit.

51:39.741 --> 51:42.781
He's not been having
a great time of it lately.

51:42.783 --> 51:43.364
I understand that.

51:43.366 --> 51:45.156
He hasn't got much longer
to live and all that.

51:45.158 --> 51:48.448
But he doesn't need
to be so touchy, you know?

51:48.450 --> 51:52.239
Jim, I'm afraid
I've got some bad news.

51:52.241 --> 51:53.448
Well, I knew that was coming.

51:53.450 --> 51:55.573
You are suffering
from a rare condition

51:55.575 --> 51:56.989
called Stendhal syndrome.

51:56.991 --> 52:00.114
Not a debilitating illness,
by any means.

52:00.116 --> 52:03.364
But you'll definitely
need to make some changes

52:03.366 --> 52:03.989
in your lifestyle.

52:03.991 --> 52:06.989
Can you explain to me
what that means?

52:06.991 --> 52:09.989
I... can.

52:09.991 --> 52:11.198
But not right now.

52:11.200 --> 52:16.448
Unfortunately, I'm late
for my next appointment.

52:16.450 --> 52:17.198
What, that's it?

52:17.200 --> 52:18.906
I'm afraid so. Time is money.

52:18.908 --> 52:22.364
But if you have any questions,
please do give me a call.

52:22.366 --> 52:24.531
Well, I have lots of questions.

52:24.533 --> 52:25.031
Goodbye, Jim.

52:25.033 --> 52:27.948
Please get some rest.
And, remember,

52:27.950 --> 52:28.864
paintings of the Baroque period

52:28.866 --> 52:32.616
should be avoided
as much as possible.

52:33.866 --> 52:36.198
Oh, and one last thing.

52:36.200 --> 52:38.989
- What?
- Caravaggio can be prickly.

52:38.991 --> 52:40.989
But he's really
not such a bad person.

52:40.991 --> 52:43.531
You're talking about a bloke
who killed someone

52:43.533 --> 52:45.281
over an argument
in a tennis match.

52:59.450 --> 53:01.698
The doctor told me
to avoid Caravaggio

53:01.700 --> 53:04.406
if I want to keep my sanity.

53:04.408 --> 53:05.656
What kind of life is that?

53:05.658 --> 53:07.739
I feel sorry for you,
I really do.

53:07.741 --> 53:09.906
I know where you're coming from.

53:09.908 --> 53:12.198
But give me
the tremendous violence

53:12.200 --> 53:14.698
of Francis Bacon any days
of the week.

53:14.700 --> 53:18.448
The screaming queen
paints a screaming pope.

53:18.450 --> 53:21.281
The human mouth
as a gaping wound.

53:21.283 --> 53:22.489
If you force me to choose,

53:22.491 --> 53:24.823
I mean, if you put a gun
to my head,

53:24.825 --> 53:25.698
I'd go for Mapplethorpe.

53:25.700 --> 53:30.031
No, his work is too cold.
There is no emotion.

53:30.033 --> 53:31.948
That man knew
how to photograph beauty.

53:31.950 --> 53:34.864
Mapplethorpe didn't understand
the men he photographed.

53:34.866 --> 53:39.323
They were reduced to what hung
between their legs.

53:39.325 --> 53:39.698
Bollocks!

53:39.700 --> 53:44.991
At the end of the day...
we're all just pieces of meat.

53:52.575 --> 53:55.239
Guys...
Guys, can someone tell me

53:55.241 --> 53:56.739
what the fuck is going on?

53:56.741 --> 53:57.406
According to our friend,

53:57.408 --> 54:00.031
you have a syndrome
named after Henry Stendhal.

54:00.033 --> 54:02.781
Stendhal syndrome
is a rare illness

54:02.783 --> 54:04.698
which affects some individuals

54:04.700 --> 54:06.906
that are exposed to fine art.

54:06.908 --> 54:08.989
It can cause dizziness,

54:08.991 --> 54:11.989
hallucinations
and even blackouts.

54:11.991 --> 54:13.614
Was this Stendhal bloke
a doctor?

54:13.616 --> 54:15.614
No. No, he was
a 19th-century novelist

54:15.616 --> 54:16.823
who wrote
The Charterhouse of Parma,

54:16.825 --> 54:20.239
amongst other things. He was
a little flowery for my taste.

54:20.241 --> 54:21.364
But you know
how the French are.

54:21.366 --> 54:25.156
Hey! Your clichéd view of my
country is 50 years out of date.

54:25.158 --> 54:29.114
We have a vibrant youth culture,
the rap scene is massive,

54:29.116 --> 54:31.864
and we have tension
in the suburbs.

54:31.866 --> 54:32.489
So go fuck yourself.

54:32.491 --> 54:35.781
"Stendhal wrote about his
experience with the phenomenon

54:35.783 --> 54:40.783
after a visit to Florence
in the summer of 1817."

54:42.241 --> 54:45.906
"Absorbed in the contemplation
of divine beauty,

54:45.908 --> 54:50.239
I could perceive
its very essence close at hand."

54:50.241 --> 54:51.823
"I could, as it were,

54:51.825 --> 54:56.450
feel the stuff of it
beneath my fingertips."

54:56.908 --> 55:01.033
Wait a minute, I've never
even been to Florence.

55:04.283 --> 55:06.575
Oh, fuck!

55:39.658 --> 55:41.114
What's going on, mate?

55:41.116 --> 55:43.698
You're late.

55:43.700 --> 55:46.823
I won't tolerate
bad timekeeping.

55:46.825 --> 55:49.114
I'm sorry. What's going on?

55:49.116 --> 55:52.073
What's going on is...
you were late.

